<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1688,1714]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Biology.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes, H. S." box="[304,470,1688,1715]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="279 - 291" refId="ref110475" refString="Lopes, H. S. (1973 b) Collecting and rearing sarcophagid flies (Diptera) in Brazil, during 40 years. Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 45, 279 - 291." type="journal article" year="1973">Lopes (1973b)</bibRefCitation>
reared this species under laboratory conditions without providing information on its development. It has been collected from human feces, chicken viscera, dead fish, dead mice, dead marine animals, rotten banana mixed with brown sugar, and rotten 
<taxonomicName box="[746,864,1760,1786]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Syagrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="comosa">
<emphasis box="[746,864,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. comosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes, H. S." box="[882,1022,1760,1786]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref110396" refString="Lopes, H. S. (1969) A Catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas South of the United States: Family Sarcophagidae. Departamento de Zoologia, Secretaria da Agricultura, 103, 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="1969">Lopes 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes, H. S." box="[1038,1191,1760,1787]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="279 - 291" refId="ref110475" refString="Lopes, H. S. (1973 b) Collecting and rearing sarcophagid flies (Diptera) in Brazil, during 40 years. Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 45, 279 - 291." type="journal article" year="1973">Lopes 1973b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mendes, J. &amp; Linhares, A. X." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="355 - 364" refId="ref112405" refString="Mendes, J. &amp; Linhares, A. X. (1993) Sazonalidade, preferencia por iscas e desenvolvimento ovariano em varias especies de Sarcophagidae (Diptera). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 37 (2), 355 - 364." type="journal article" year="1993">Mendes &amp; Linhares 1993</bibRefCitation>
). Malaise and Shannon traps have been used to collect this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes, H. S. &amp; Tibana, R." box="[972,1221,1796,1822]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="151 - 157" refId="ref110007" refString="Lopes, H. S. &amp; Tibana, R. (1991) Sarcophagidae (Diptera) de Roraima, Brasil. Acta Amazonica, 21, 151 - 157. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 1809 - 43921991211157" type="journal article" year="1991">Lopes &amp; Tibana 1991</bibRefCitation>
). At 
<collectingRegion box="[1274,1436,1796,1822]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
Zoological Garden, it was collected using a wind-oriented trap (W.O.T.) baited with rotten liver (
<bibRefCitation author="Oliveira, V. C. &amp; D'Almeida, J. M. &amp; Paes, M. &amp; Sanavria, A." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="191 - 196" refId="ref113517" refString="Oliveira, V. C., D'Almeida, J. M., Paes, M. J &amp; Sanavria, A. (2002) Population dynamics of calyptrate Diptera (Muscidae and Sarcophagidae) at the Rio-Zoo Foundation, Rio de Janeiro, RJ, Brazil. Brazilian Journal of Biology, 62 (2), 191 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1519 - 69842002000200002" type="journal article" year="2002">
Oliveira 
<emphasis box="[1377,1437,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
